This paper presents a machine learning algorithm for achieving autonomous control and intelligent decision making in a bipedal walking robot. The paper focuses on the application of reinforcement learning algorithm called Deep Deterministic Policy Gradient (DDPG) to achieve stable bipedal walking. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is Robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms such as supervised learning, imitation learning, and reinforcement learning, which are commonly used in the sub-domains of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also uses a realistic robotics simulator, Gazebo, which falls under the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper compares the gait pattern of the bipedal walker with the actual human walking pattern, which involves computer vision techniques and falls under the sub-category of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV).
